\title{Skill Installer}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{Install Codex skills into $CODEX_HOME/skills from a curated list or a GitHub repo path. Use when a user asks to list installable skills, install a curated skill, or install a skill from another repo (including private repos).}

\subtree{
\title{Skill Installer}
\p{Helps install skills. By default these are from https://github.com/openai/skills/tree/main/skills/.curated, but users can also provide other locations.}

\p{Use the helper scripts based on the task:}

\ul{
\li{List curated skills when the user asks what is available, or if the user uses this skill without specifying what to do.}
\li{Install from the curated list when the user provides a skill name.}
\li{Install from another repo when the user provides a GitHub repo/path (including private repos).}
}

\p{Install skills with the helper scripts.}

\subtree{
\title{Communication}
\p{When listing curated skills, output approximately as follows, depending on the context of the user's request: """ Skills from {repo}:}

\ol{
\li{skill-1}
\li{skill-2 (already installed)}
\li{...}
}

\p{Which ones would you like installed? """}

\p{After installing a skill, tell the user: "Restart Codex to pick up new skills."}
}

\subtree{
\title{Scripts}
\p{All of these scripts use network, so when running in the sandbox, request escalation when running them.}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb scripts/list-curated-skills.py\stopverb} (prints curated list with installed annotations)}
\li{\code{\startverb scripts/list-curated-skills.py --format json\stopverb}}
\li{\code{\startverb scripts/install-skill-from-github.py --repo <owner>/<repo> --path <path/to/skill> [<path/to/skill> ...]\stopverb}}
\li{\code{\startverb scripts/install-skill-from-github.py --url https://github.com/<owner>/<repo>/tree/<ref>/<path>\stopverb}}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Behavior and Options}
\ul{
\li{Defaults to direct download for public GitHub repos.}
\li{If download fails with auth/permission errors, falls back to git sparse checkout.}
\li{Aborts if the destination skill directory already exists.}
\li{Installs into \code{\startverb $CODEX_HOME/skills/<skill-name>\stopverb} (defaults to \code{\startverb ~/.codex/skills\stopverb}).}
\li{Multiple \code{\startverb --path\stopverb} values install multiple skills in one run, each named from the path basename unless \code{\startverb --name\stopverb} is supplied.}
\li{Options: \code{\startverb --ref <ref>\stopverb} (default \code{\startverb main\stopverb}), \code{\startverb --dest <path>\stopverb}, \code{\startverb --method auto|download|git\stopverb}.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Notes}
\ul{
\li{Curated listing is fetched from \code{\startverb https://github.com/openai/skills/tree/main/skills/.curated\stopverb} via the GitHub API. If it is unavailable, explain the error and exit.}
\li{Private GitHub repos can be accessed via existing git credentials or optional \code{\startverb GITHUB_TOKEN\stopverb}/\code{\startverb GH_TOKEN\stopverb} for download.}
\li{Git fallback tries HTTPS first, then SSH.}
\li{The skills at https://github.com/openai/skills/tree/main/skills/.system are preinstalled, so no need to help users install those. If they ask, just explain this. If they insist, you can download and overwrite.}
\li{Installed annotations come from \code{\startverb $CODEX_HOME/skills\stopverb}.}
}
}
}